ing on the earth. For the LORD God had not yet sent rain to water the earth, and there were no people to cultivate the soil."}, {:version=>"English Standard Version", :text=>"When no bush of the field was yet in the land and no small plant of the field had yet sprung up—for the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the land, and there was no man to work the ground,"}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"Now no shrub of the field had yet appeared on the earth, nor had any plant of the field sprouted; for the LORD God had not yet sent rain upon the earth, and there was no man to cultivate the ground."}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"Now no shrub of the field was yet in the earth, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted, for the LORD God had not sent rain upon the earth, and there was no man to cultivate the ground."}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"before any plant of the field was in the earth and before any herb of the field had grown. For the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the earth, and "}, {:version=>" no man to till the ground;", :text=>"King James Bible"}, {:version=>"And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and ", :text=>" not a man to till the ground."}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"no shrub of the field had yet grown on the land, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted, for the LORD God had not made it rain on the land, and there was no man to work the ground."}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"no grass or plants were growing anywhere. God had not yet sent any rain, and there was no one to work the land. "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"there were no plants on the earth and no seeds had sprouted, because he had not sent any rain, and there was no one to cultivate the land; "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"No shrub of the field had yet grown on the land, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted, for the LORD God had not made it rain on the land, and there was no man to work the ground. "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"no shrubs had yet grown in the meadows of the earth and no vegetation had sprouted, because the LORD God had not sent rain on the earth and there were no human beings to work the ground. "}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"Now no shrub of the field had yet grown on the earth, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted, for the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the earth, and there was no man to cultivate the ground."}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"Now no bush of the field was yet in the land, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted; for the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the land, and there were no people to cultivate the ground,"}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"Wild bushes and plants were not on the earth yet because the LORD God hadn't sent rain on the earth. Also, there was no one to farm the land."}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"No shrub of the field was yet in the earth, and no herb of the field had yet sprung up; for the LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground;"}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"Now no shrub of the field was yet in the earth, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted, for the LORD God had not sent rain upon the earth; and there was no man to cultivate the ground."}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground."}, {:version=>"American King James Version", :text=>"And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground."}, {:version=>"American Standard Version", :text=>"And no plant of the field was yet in the earth, and no herb of the field had yet sprung up; for Jehovah God had not caused it to rain upon the earth: and there was not a man to till the ground;"}, {:version=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation", :text=>"and every herb of the field before it was on the earth, and all the grass of the field before it sprang up, for God had not rained on the earth, and there was not a man to cultivate it."}, {:version=>"Douay-Rheims Bible", :text=>"And every plant of the field before it spring up in the earth, and every herb of the ground before it grew: for the Lord God had not rained upon the earth; and there was not a man to till the earth. "}, {:version=>"Darby Bible Translation", :text=>"and every shrub of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew; for Jehovah Elohim had not caused it to rain on the earth, and there was no man to till the ground."}, {:version=>"English Revised Version", :text=>"And no plant of the field was yet in the earth, and no herb of the field had yet sprung up: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground;"}, {:version=>"Webster's Bible Translation", :text=>"And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground."}, {:version=>"World English Bible", :text=>"No plant of the field was yet in the earth, and no herb of the field had yet sprung up; for Yahweh God had not caused it to rain on the earth. There was not a man to till the ground,"}, {:version=>"Young's Literal Translation", :text=>" and no shrub of the field is yet in the earth, and no herb of the field yet sprouteth, for Jehovah God hath not rained upon the earth, and a man there is not to serve the ground,"}]}